  "recommendation_html": "<p><b>Net-Sharpe lift on sparse Ledoit-Wolf (gross Sharpe 6.87, vol 10.32%):</b></p><ul><li>IBKR Fixed (baseline): net Sharpe <b>4.71</b></li><li>Commission-free, zero PFOF penalty (upper bound): net Sharpe <b>5.51</b>  (\u0394 +0.80)</li><li>Commission-free, 1.3\u00d7 bid-ask (realistic PFOF): net Sharpe <b>5.39</b>  (\u0394 +0.68)</li><li>Commission-free, 2.0\u00d7 bid-ask (worst-case PFOF): net Sharpe <b>5.11</b>  (\u0394 +0.40)</li><li>Tastytrade ($1 open / $0 close, direct routing): net Sharpe <b>4.90</b>  (\u0394 +0.18)</li></ul><p><b>Recommendation \u2014 Tastytrade is the winner for this portfolio.</b> Tastytrade keeps DIRECT routing (same fill quality as IBKR), caps per-leg commissions at $10, charges nothing to close, and supports portfolio margin at $125k+. It delivers ~76% of the commission savings vs IBKR Fixed with ZERO PFOF penalty. Alpaca/Robinhood commission savings are real but the combination of PFOF fill quality degradation and (critically) no portfolio margin means the 3\u00d7-leverage config cannot actually be executed on those platforms. The Sharpe table makes this concrete: at a realistic 1.3\u00d7 PFOF penalty, Alpaca nets Sharpe 5.39 vs Tastytrade 4.90 \u2014 and that Alpaca number assumes you can somehow run 3\u00d7 leverage without portfolio margin, which you cannot.</p><p><b>Do NOT use Robinhood</b> for this strategy: no native multi-leg support is a disqualifier for credit spreads, and the documented PFOF penalty is the worst of any free broker.</p><p><b>Second-order optimisation \u2014 tiered IBKR.</b> If the book runs more than 10k contracts/month, IBKR Pro Tiered drops the effective commission from $0.65 to ~$0.25 per contract. That would cut the commission drag from 8.27%/yr to ~3.18%/yr \u2014 a net-Sharpe lift of roughly +0.50 above the current IBKR Fixed baseline. Worth engaging the IBKR relationship manager once live volume justifies it.</p><p><b>Bottom line.</b> The biggest realistic Sharpe lift from changing brokers is ~0.5 (Tastytrade or IBKR Tiered). That is real and worth capturing, but it does NOT close the gap between the EXP-2450 honest net Sharpe 4.71 and the original Sharpe > 6.0 target. Broker choice is a tail-optimisation, not a strategy fix.</p>"
}